                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.841 Surtax/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-31T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 31—6:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to [the Department’s] August 17, 3 p.m., and other telegrams exchanged
                    between this office and the Legation. It is published in today’s vernacular
                    press that the surtax tonnage dues have been abolished. This has been confirmed
                    verbally by the Commissioner of Foreign Affairs to me as being effective
                    September 1st.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
